<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[71874]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[The architecture of Oksar Hansen, at the MACBA]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Architecture.</strong> The exhibition on the work of Polish architect Oskar Hansen (1922-2005) focuses on the development of his Open Form theory.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>As part of the MACBA&#8217;s interest in understanding the role of architecture in the expression of orthodox external modernity, this exhibition on the work of Polish architect Oskar Hansen (1922-2005) focuses on the development of his Open Form theory. From its beginnings, this &#8220;attitude&#8221; (more than just a theory) was conceived as a tool for designing architectural projects. Its development and application in the fields of teaching art, editing films, visual games and performance practices gave rise to a wide range of experiments that place the creator&#8217;s centre of attention on interacting with others, exchange and the socialisation of the artistic object.</p>
